  "prompt": "What consumer startups have real technology?",
  "response": "The term \"real technology\" can be somewhat subjective, but typically refers to companies that have developed significant and proprietary technological advancements or innovations. Here are a few consumer startups known for their real technological contributions:\n\n1. **Tesla**: Though not exactly a startup anymore, Tesla has profoundly impacted the consumer automotive market with its electric vehicle technology and autonomous driving capabilities.\n\n2. **SpaceX**: In the realm of space exploration and consumer space travel, SpaceX has advanced reusable rocket technology that significantly lowers launch costs.\n\n3. **Stripe**: Stripe is a financial technology company that provides secure and scalable online payment processing services. It\u2019s known for its robust API and developer-friendly tools.\n\n4. **Beyond Meat**: This company has developed plant-based meat products that mimic the taste and texture of real meat, appealing to vegetarians and environmentalists alike.\n\n5. **Rivian**: An electric vehicle startup, Rivian focuses on electric trucks and SUVs, but its battery technology and autonomous capabilities are noteworthy.\n\n6. **Magic Leap**: Specializes in augmented reality (AR) technologies and has developed AR headsets with spatial computing capabilities.\n\n7. **Juul**: While controversial, Juul's e-cigarette technology has indeed transformed the vaping industry with advanced pod-based vaporizer designs.\n\n8. **Peloton**: Known for its exercise equipment and streaming workout classes, Peloton incorporates real-time data and community aspects into its high-tech fitness products.\n\n9. **Robinhood**: This fintech startup has democratized investing with its commission-free trades and user-friendly mobile app, driven by complex algorithms and high-frequency trading technologies.\n\n10. **Instacart**: Utilizing complex algorithms, Instacart provides grocery delivery services with real-time data processing and logistics management.\n\n11. **Ro**: A telehealth startup that utilizes advanced data analytics and telemedicine technology to provide healthcare services directly to consumers.\n\nThese examples highlight startups across various industries, each leveraging technology to revolutionize their respective markets.",
